{
  "texts": [
    "global) first-order correspondent of φ over standard full possibility frames, then ψ ↓ is a local (resp.",
    "global) first-order correspondent of φ over all full possibility frames.Proof.",
    "Given a full possibility frame F = ⟨S, ⊑, {R i } i∈I, P ⟩, define F ↓ = ⟨S, ⊑, {R i↓ } i∈I, P ⟩ by xR i↓ y iff ∃y ′: xR i y ′ and y ⊑ y ′.",
    "Then it is easy to check that F ↓ is a full possibility frame, and F ↓ satisfies R-down by construction, so it is a standard possibility frame.",
    "Moreover, the identity map on S is a surjective robust possibility morphism from F to F ↓, so these frames validate exactly the same formulas by Proposition 3.7."
  ]
}